	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, Dec 10th 7:22 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I have devoted myself for many months now to figure out how a wizard could safely solo without having to have buffs from other classes.&nbsp;&nbsp;I think I have finally discovered the setup that needs to be used.  Please read all of this before you tell me I am insane.<br><br>Wizards are often told that they should not want anything except int items so that they can have as much mana as possible.  This tradition has caused the wizard to become totally dependant on groups and unable for a wizard to be able to strike out on their own.  This is an error that needs to be corrected.<br><br>After trying every kind of setup that I can imagine, I finally stumbled across a type of setup where it became very easy to solo.  At the core of this setup is AGILITY.  Before you tell me I am nuts, try this out:<br><br>2 Serpentine Bracers +9 Agi +3 Dex... Around 50pp each<br>1 SilverSilk Leggins +4 Agi +12 HP... Around 75pp each<br><br>Many people have never considered putting these items on their wizards because they can find int items that can go there.  But on my lvl 24 wizard I traded a total of 6 int for a total of 22 agi, 6 dex, and 12hp.  I have never looked back.  The rest of your setup can be for INT like you normally do.<br><br>The major weakness to a wizard is that we do not have a pet until very very high levels (lvl 55 I think).  Other classes have a pet or melee ability so that they do not ever run into the problems that we do.  The agility does raise our AC but the real power comes from our sudden ability to DODGE ATTACKS AND CAUSE ENEMIES TO MISS.  This prevents them from interrupting your casting so often and gives you that wonderful chance to root them and back away to nuke again.  What good is it to have a little extra mana if you cannot ever use it because your casting keeps getting interrupted?<br><br>Try it out... It is also a dream come true for wizards that like to duel because suddenly your opponent is not able to hit you easily anymore.  I am NOT saying that Agi is now more importiant than INT.  But what I am saying is that all INT will force you to forever be in a group and never get all that great exp that can be earned when you solo.<br><br>The stupidity that has gone into our setups ever since this game was created is truly sickening.  Has nobody else realized that a wizard is using the same setups that other pure casters use?  Why should we be using the same setups when we have no pet to protect us?  Think about it... I want all of you to please give some insight into this.  This is an ongoing research and I hope to bring updates and improvements as I go.<br><br>Love,<br>Alexandri Tigress (Erollsi Marr Server)<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
