	   <tr><td colspan=2>Thank you.&nbsp;&nbsp;A friend of mine offered a thought that I had not yet considered.  Check this out.. this is mostly a thought for high level people who have the money to do it:<br><br>Loam Encrusted Robe<br>+5 int +10 Agi +10 Dex +10 SVMagic +80 mana<br><br>I am unsure of the price of this item, but it is dropped in the Hole by a lvl 57 mob.  So I am pretty sure that this item does not come cheap but may be a wizards dream.  The whole point of INT on a wizard is really to add more mana.  I think this robe gives you enough extra mana to offset the reduced amount of INT.  My wizard would have a total of 117 Agi with this robe.  The added DEX is a nice touch too... Somewhere I remember reading that DEX helps you "recover and continue casting" while AGI helps you dodge the attacks to begin with.  I am wanting to compare the effectiveness of this robe to the effectiveness of Shining Metallic Robes (+9 int +8 SVFire +8 SVCold).  We are given many defensive spells, but on my wizard there is a "hole" in the SVMagic Department.  If I am correct about what spells are in that group, then that means that such spells as roots and enchantment attacks are in that group.  So that gives (on a personal basis only) points toward the Loam Encrusted Robe.  Keep talking to me people... This is getting good.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
